PMC3 rewind event. A rewind happens when a speculative event (such as latency or CPI stack) is selected on PMC3 and the stall reason or reload source did not match the one programmed in PMC3. When this occurs, the count in PMC3 will not change.
Larx finished

The processor's data cache was reloaded from local core's L2 hit without dispatch conflicts on Mepf state due to a demand load

Internal LSU reject from LRQ. Rejects cause the load to go back to LRQ, but it stays contained within the LSU once it gets issued. This event counts the number of times the LRQ attempts to relaunch an instruction after a reject. Any load can suffer multiple rejects
Initial and Final Pump Scope was group pump (prediction=correct) for an instruction fetch (demand only)
Non FMA instruction completed
